    \begin {tikzcd}
      \displaystyle \coprod _{C(x, y)\times  Fy} C(c, x)\ar [r, shift
      left=.2em]\ar [r, shift right=.2em] & \displaystyle \coprod _{Fx} C(c, x)\ar [r, two heads] &
      Fc\makebox [0pt][l]{.}
    \end {tikzcd}


 Since colimits in \hat {C} are computed pointwise, we conclude
  that F is the colimit of contravariant hom-functors as pictured.
  By the construction of colimits, this diagram equivalently
  determines the colimit of a diagram J\xrightarrow {D} Set whose objects are
  \coprod _{Fx} and whose morphisms are \coprod _{C(x, y)\times  Fy}, with
  domain the chosen element of Fy and codomain the corresponding element of
  Fx (noticing the contravariance of F). This is exactly the category of
  elements of F. Noticing that the sets C(c, x) are exactly the
  images of x under y, F is now equivalently the colimit of the
  diagram \text {el}(F)\xrightarrow {\Pi } C\xhookrightarrow {y} \hat {C}.

